<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Visualization">Visualizatio=
n</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBox_plot&a=
mp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Visualization"><s=
pan>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></=
div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Boxplot_vs_PDF.svg" class=3D"mw-file-descript=
ion"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/=
Boxplot_vs_PDF.svg/330px-Boxplot_vs_PDF.svg.png" decoding=3D"async" width=
=3D"300" height=3D"327" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"598" d=
ata-file-height=3D"652"></a><figcaption>Box-plot and a <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_density_function" title=3D"Probability den=
sity function">probability density function</a> (pdf) of a Normal N(0,1=CF=
=83<sup>2</sup>) Population</figcaption></figure>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Boxplots_with_skewness.png" class=3D"mw-file-=
description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thu=
mb/2/2a/Boxplots_with_skewness.png/250px-Boxplots_with_skewness.png" decodi=
ng=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"211" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-fi=
le-width=3D"605" data-file-height=3D"510"></a><figcaption>Box-plots display=
ing the skewness of the data set</figcaption></figure>
<p>Although box plots may seem more primitive than <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Histogram" title=3D"Histogram">histograms</a> or <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kernel_density_estimation" title=3D"Kerne=
l density estimation">kernel density estimates</a>, they do have a number o=
f advantages. First, the box plot enables statisticians to do a quick graph=
ical examination on one or more data sets. Box-plots also take up less spac=
e and are therefore particularly useful for comparing distributions between=
 several groups or sets of data in parallel. Lastly, the overall structure =
of histograms and kernel density estimate can be strongly influenced by the=
 choice of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histogram#Number_of_bin=
s_and_width" title=3D"Histogram">number and width of bins</a> techniques an=
d the choice of bandwidth, respectively.
</p><p>Although looking at a statistical distribution is more common than l=
ooking at a box plot, it can be useful to compare the box plot against the =
probability density function (theoretical histogram) for a normal N(0,<i>=
=CF=83</i><sup>2</sup>) distribution and observe their characteristics dire=
ctly.
</p>
